","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Fanciful spelling of   Gail  , also occasionally written  <b>Gaelle</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"Gail","meanings":["Shortened form of   Abigail .  It was not found as an independent given name before the middle of the 20th century; it became popular in the 1950s and 1960s, but has since fallen out of fashion."]}]},{"name":"Morda","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Anglicized form of Scottish Gaelic <i>Muirne</i>, originally a byname meaning ‘beloved’; borne by Fingal's mother in the Ossianic poems of  James Macpherson  (  compare  Malvina  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Myrna","meanings":["Anglicized form of Gaelic Muirne , now also used elsewhere in the English-speaking world. It is associated with the American film star  Myrna Loy  (  1905–93 )."]},{"name":"Muirne","meanings":["Traditional name, originally a byname meaning ‘beloved’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sadhb Ingen Mael Morda O'Domnaill was born about 1033, in Leinster, Ireland, her father, MAEL MORDA Ó DOMNAILL, was 15 and her mother, CAILLEACH INGEN FAELIN, was 13. She married King Donncuan MacDunlainge O'Toole about 1053, in Leinster, Ireland. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died about 1082, in Ireland, at the age of 51."},"et":{"about 1033–about 1082":"umbes 1033–umbes 1082","1033–1082":"1033–1082","1030–1096":"1030–1096","1020–1090":"1020–1090","1055–1119":"1055–1119","1022–Female":"1022–Surnud","about 1082":"umbes 1082","1090":"1090","1022":"1022","1055":"1055","1033":"1033","1020":"1020","1096":"1096","1030":"1030","1082":"1082","about 1053":"umbes 1053","about 1033":"umbes 1033","about 1055":"umbes 1055","1119":"1119","Leinster, Dublin, Ireland":"Diocese of Dublin, Iirimaa","Ireland":"Iirimaa","Leinster, Ireland":"Leinster, Iirimaa"},"fi":{"about 1033–about 1082":"noin 1033–noin 1082"